ðŸ§© Step 1: What is Vector3?
--> In Unity, Vector3 is a structure that stores three numbers:
 Vector3 position = new Vector3(x, y, z); -> These three numbers represent position or direction in 3D space.
Example:-
Vector3 playerPosition = new Vector3(3, 2, 5);
This means:
Move 3 units right , 2 units up , 5 units forward
So it defines one point in space

| Expression               | Meaning                       | Example     |
| ------------------------ | ----------------------------- | ----------- |
| `B - A`                  | Direction (vector from A â†’ B) | `(3, 0, 4)` |
| `(B - A).magnitude`      | Distance (number)             | `5`         |
| `Vector3.Distance(A, B)` | Shortcut for above            | `5`         |

-->Unity Example: Move in Multiple Directions

using UnityEngine;

public class CombineVectorsMovement : MonoBehaviour
{
    public float moveSpeed = 5f;

    void Update()
    {
        Vector3 moveDir = Vector3.zero;

        if (Input.GetKey(KeyCode.W))
            moveDir += Vector3.forward;  // forward

        if (Input.GetKey(KeyCode.S))
            moveDir += Vector3.back;     // backward

        if (Input.GetKey(KeyCode.A))
            moveDir += Vector3.left;     // left

        if (Input.GetKey(KeyCode.D))
            moveDir += Vector3.right;    // right

        // Normalize so diagonal speed is consistent
        moveDir = moveDir.normalized;

        transform.position += moveDir * moveSpeed * Time.deltaTime;
    }


}
